Yes. I’d create one templates/ks/*.ks.j2 per profile, and use small Jinja conditionals where RHEL 7 needs a different include than RHEL 8/9/10.

Big rule: don’t include partials/170-post/empty.ks.j2 when you are also including real post scripts. empty is only for “no post actions.”

Also, since these include sshd-enabled, make sure the selected package partials install openssh-server. Add openssh-clients too if you want the installed system to be able to run the ssh command outbound.

